    <title>Creating Cinder Volumes for Boot Images</title>
    <shortdesc>You can create Cinder volumes to store VM boot images. </shortdesc>
    <prolog><author/>
        <author/>
    </prolog>
    <body>
        <context id="context_N1001F_N1001C_N10001">
            <p>The use of Cinder volumes is recommended for fast instance booting.</p>
        </context>
        <ol>
            <step id="step_N1002B_N10028_N1001C_N10001">
                <cmd>Log in as the appropriate tenant.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10034_N10028_N1001C_N10001">
                <cmd>On the <uicontrol>Project</uicontrol> menu, open the
                        <uicontrol>Compute</uicontrol> section, and then click
                        <uicontrol>Volumes</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10049_N10028_N1001C_N10001">
                <cmd>On the <wintitle>Volumes</wintitle> page, click <uicontrol>Create
                        Volume</uicontrol></cmd>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10059_N10028_N1001C_N10001">
                <cmd>Complete the <wintitle>Create Volume</wintitle> form.</cmd>
                
                    <p>For an example, see the <cite>HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Reference Deployment Scenarios:
                            Creating a Volume</cite>.</p>
                    <!-- p>For settings information, see <xref href="jow1439393574682.xml"/>.</p -->
                
            </step>
        </ol>
    </body>
</task-wr>